  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (e4a2915 2022-06-20T00:04:23.839115Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --fork-url <url>\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n* Start Anvil process in Fork mode\r\n* Make scripts that makes requests using an HTTP connection against the Anvil process (such as when using web3.py)\r\n* Notice Anvil process errors out\r\n\r\n```\r\nthread 'fork-backend-thread' panicked at 'Failed to get block hash for 14998061\r\nblock 14998061 not found', /Users/runner/work/foundry/foundry/evm/src/executor/fork/backend.rs:310:33\r\nstack backtrace:\r\n   0:        0x107d76319 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   1:        0x107ac81eb - __mh_execute_header\r\n   2:        0x107d4bba8 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   3:        0x107d7958d - __mh_execute_header\r\n   4:        0x107d7a330 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   5:        0x107d79eb4 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   6:        0x107d79e29 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   7:        0x107d79de5 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   8:        0x107e01c93 - __mh_execute_header\r\n   9:        0x1077abd47 - __mh_execute_header\r\n  10:        0x1077f1e6e - __mh_execute_header\r\n  11:        0x1077ba1d3 - __mh_execute_header\r\n  12:        0x1077bc575 - __mh_execute_header\r\n  13:        0x107d7b189 - __mh_execute_header\r\n  14:     0x7ff8196ba4e1 - __pthread_start\r\n```\r\n\r\npossible related to https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/1902",
