    "body": "by default, we fork off the \"latest\" block,\r\n\r\nbut this error occurs when requesting the block hash of the latest block fails, basically the `Block` response has no hash field yet.\r\n\r\nwhich would indicate that there's some latency somewhere within the provider's client I think\r\n\r\nperhaps we should select the \"latest\" block that already has a hash when queried via `eth_getBlockByHash` when launching anvil in fork mode",
